From: <you>
Subject: [PATCH] advertise truecolor via COLORTERM to child processes

st renders 24-bit color but never tells its children that it does.
Programs such as Textual/Rich gate 24-bit output on the COLORTERM
environment variable and fall back to the 256-color palette when it is
unset, which (among other things) breaks Kitty-graphics Unicode
placeholders, since those encode the image id in a truecolor foreground.

Set COLORTERM=truecolor in execsh(), right where TERM is already set, so
the shell and everything it launches inherit it -- the same thing kitty
and other modern terminals do. Use overwrite=0 instead of 1 if you would
rather respect a COLORTERM value inherited from st's own environment.
---
diff --git a/st.c b/st.c
index 12f1a29..fa758b3 100644
--- a/st.c
+++ b/st.c
@@ -796,6 +796,7 @@ execsh(char *cmd, char **args)
 	setenv("SHELL", sh, 1);
 	setenv("HOME", pw->pw_dir, 1);
 	setenv("TERM", termname, 1);
+	setenv("COLORTERM", "truecolor", 1);
 
 	signal(SIGCHLD, SIG_DFL);
 	signal(SIGHUP, SIG_DFL);
